Dead wood stocks and fluxes for Barro Colorado Island 50-ha forest dynamic plot, 2017-2024

Lily F. Pitcher and Helene C. Muller-Landau

2025-07-23

Study site and sample design

This document reports the estimated above ground Coarse deadwood stocks of dead trees in the 50ha plot of Barrow Colorado Island, STRI, Panama. Woody debris is estimated for 100 (40X40m) within the 50ha through annual field studies which comprised of the following studies:

Coarse Woody Debris (CWD) dynamics: CWD is defined as deadwood with a diameter equal or greater than 200cm. Four 40-m transects, 2 in each of 2 perpendicular directions, span each 40x40 m subplot. For fallen deadwood pieces the diameter is measured at the point where the piece crosses the transect.In addition, each piece is marked to allow it to be tracked over time and distinguished from newly fallen debris in the next census. We also record the tag number of the tree from which the piece came, if discernible. We also categorize into branch or trunk. We inventory standing dead trees within the 40x40 sub-plots.For each standing dead tree greater than 200 mm in diameter, we measure dbh and height. In addition, we categorize the abundance of branches remaining (<10 %, 10 – 90 % or > 90 %). In the case of stumps, we measure diameter at half way between the top and ground. We try to record the tag.

Further details of sampling design and protocols can be found here:

https://forestgeo.si.edu/protocols/woody-debris

Calculations of CWD stocks and fluxes

This report calculates annual stocks and fluxes of standing and fallen coarse woody debris. The data were formatted and cleaned prior to loading into this report using the code clean0_bci50deadwood_rawtoformatted.RMD and clean1_bci50deadwood_formattedtocorrected.Rmd. Calculations for individual sample pieces are conducted in density_calculation_bci50deadwood_correctedtoprocessed.Rmd. Explanations of all calculations and further information can be found in CalculationExplanation_for_deadwoodStocks&Fluxes.pdf.

Estimated mean stocks and fluxes of fallen and standing CWD calculated by first averaging over the one hundred 40 x 40 m dynamics plots, then averaging over years (2017-2024). Estimated total stocks of deadwood (Mean Total), and estimated annual deadwood input (Mean Input) for both volume and mass per ha. Residence time represents the average residence time of dead wood in the plot which is calculated as mean stocks divided by the mean inputs.
